        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1958-06-11T07:59:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1958-06-11T07:59:00-05:00" n="68"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d68">
                <head>68. Memorandum of a Telephone Conversation Between the Secretary of State and
                    the Chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff (<persName corresp="#p_TGNF1"
                        >Twining</persName>), Washington, June 11, 1958, 8:59 a.m.<note n="1"
                        type="source" xml:id="d68fn1">Source: Eisenhower Library, <persName
                            corresp="#p_DJF1">Dulles</persName> Papers, General Telephone
                        Conversations. Transcribed in <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">Dulles</persName>’
                        office by <persName corresp="#p_BPD1">Phyllis D. Bernau</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" type="conversation-or-meeting-date"
                            when="1958-06-11T08:59:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 11, 1958, 8:59 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">TELEPHONE CALL TO GENERAL <persName corresp="#p_TGNF1"
                        >TWINING</persName>
                </p>
                <p>The Sec said the Pres, the PM and he had quite a talk at the WH re Lebanon. The
                    Sec thought T should know it is tensing up quite considerably there and we sent
                    a message to <persName corresp="#p_CC7">Chamoun</persName> on behalf of the Pres
                    and PM which reaffirms assurances given.<note n="2" xml:id="d68fn2">
                        <ref target="#d67">
                            <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>
                        </ref>.</note> T wondered about extra measures—they are on a 48-hour basis.
                    The Pres, said the Sec, said to raise with T whether it should be a 24-hour
                    basis. T will look into it this a.m. It looks as though the Soviets will veto
                    the res in the SC,<note n="3" xml:id="d68fn3">See <ref target="#d66">Document
                            66</ref>.</note> said the Sec, and that may bring things to a head. We
                    may follow up by calling in the <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss>.</p>
            </div>
